{"section": "3.9.1: Divisibility proof by induction.", "qid": 0, "instructions": "<div class=\"activity-instructions\">\n <p>\n  <b>\n   Theorem:\n  </b>\n  For every positive integer n, 4 evenly divides 3\n  <sup>\n   2n\n  </sup>\n  - 1.\n </p>\n</div>\n", "question": "<div class=\"question\">\n <div class=\"setup flex-row\">\n  <div class=\"label\">\n   1)\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"text\">\n   Suppose that an inductive proof of the theorem uses the following  inductive hypothesis: For positive integer k, 4 evenly divides 3\n   <sup>\n    2k\n   </sup>\n   - 1. Which statement is equivalent to the inductive hypothesis?\n  </div>\n </div>\n <fieldset>\n  <div class=\"zb-radio-button orange orange ember-view\" id=\"ember76\" style=\"\">\n   <input aria-label=\"For some integer m,\n4m = 32k.\" name=\"11\" type=\"radio\" value=\"&lt;(unknown):ember75&gt;\"/>\n   <label aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"\">\n    For some integer m,\n4m = 3\n    <sup>\n     2k\n    </sup>\n    .\n   </label>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"zb-radio-button orange orange ember-view\" id=\"ember78\" style=\"\">\n   <input aria-label=\"For some integer m,\n3m = 32k - 1.\" name=\"11\" type=\"radio\" value=\"&lt;(unknown):ember77&gt;\"/>\n   <label aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"\">\n    For some integer m,\n3m = 3\n    <sup>\n     2k\n    </sup>\n    - 1.\n   </label>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"zb-radio-button orange orange ember-view\" id=\"ember80\" style=\"\">\n   <input aria-label=\"For some integer m,\n4m + 1 = 32k.\" name=\"11\" type=\"radio\" value=\"&lt;(unknown):ember79&gt;\"/>\n   <label aria-hidden=\"true\" style=\"\">\n    For some integer m,\n4m + 1 = 3\n    <sup>\n     2k\n    </sup>\n    .\n   </label>\n  </div>\n </fieldset>\n</div>\n", "choices": ["<div class=\"zb-radio-button orange orange ember-view\" id=\"ember76\">\n <input aria-label=\"For some integer m,\n4m = 32k.\" name=\"11\" type=\"radio\" value=\"&lt;(unknown):ember75&gt;\"/>\n <label aria-hidden=\"true\">\n  For some integer m,\n4m = 3\n  <sup>\n   2k\n  </sup>\n  .\n </label>\n</div>\n", "<div class=\"zb-radio-button orange orange ember-view\" id=\"ember78\">\n <input aria-label=\"For some integer m,\n3m = 32k - 1.\" name=\"11\" type=\"radio\" value=\"&lt;(unknown):ember77&gt;\"/>\n <label aria-hidden=\"true\">\n  For some integer m,\n3m = 3\n  <sup>\n   2k\n  </sup>\n  - 1.\n </label>\n</div>\n", "<div class=\"zb-radio-button orange orange ember-view\" id=\"ember80\">\n <input aria-label=\"For some integer m,\n4m + 1 = 32k.\" name=\"11\" type=\"radio\" value=\"&lt;(unknown):ember79&gt;\"/>\n <label aria-hidden=\"true\">\n  For some integer m,\n4m + 1 = 3\n  <sup>\n   2k\n  </sup>\n  .\n </label>\n</div>\n"], "answer": "For some integer m,\n4m + 1 = 32k.", "explanation": "<div aria-atomic=\"true\" class=\"explanation has-explanation correct\" role=\"alert\">\n <p class=\"message\">\n  Correct\n </p>\n If 4 evenly divides 3\n <sup>\n  2k\n </sup>\n - 1, then 3\n <sup>\n  2k\n </sup>\n - 1 = 4m for some integer m. Adding 1 to both sides results in the equation 4m + 1 = 3\n <sup>\n  2k\n </sup>\n .\n</div>\n"}